<div><h3>MUSC 100 - Studying Music Historically and Critically </h3>  <hr>This course is designed to introduce music majors and minors to the historical and critical study of music.  It is required for all music majors and minors.  In this course, you explore key musical works from a range of periods, genres, and styles. By getting know and understand them though listening, analysis, criticism and contextual history, you will develop the knowledge base and the methodological tool-kit needed for more advanced coursework in music.  Since the course is designed for students who anticipate majoring or minoring in music, it is expected that students enrolling in the course will have some musical background and basic music-reading skills.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> MUSC 121 or permission<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every year<br><br></div>		</td>
